<br>
Now comes PoP.  Only one spell is vendor sold 61+.  None of the new pets.  Focus item spells were included in parchment turn in spells.  HUGE amounts of NPC levels are lost as I get higher.  I know lots of mages and other casters on my server that shot right up to level 65, and have like 4 new spells overall.  With the loss of mob levels, tons of zones fall off the map for usefullness.  I started asking myself &quot;is it all worth it?&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm a 60th mage (again) with epic.  I can now solo in tons of zones for very nice exp.  I can also still travel to PoP zones and be desired in groups.  When my 45-60 friends ask for help I can help them and still reap rewards while doing it.  Like yesterday when a guild cleric and I duo fought our way through all the fire giants in Sol B to Naggy's lair, getting exp all the way.  Or when I'm bored and I want to go on a binge killing everything in sight in Lower Guk.  I still get exp.  There are lots of solo spots in PoJ for exp, and I'm still wanted for trials and groups there.<br>
<br>
I won a few parchments, turned them in and got level 62 spells.  I put them up for sale in the bazaar and got 8k each.  I now have 25k total in the bank with no immediate needs.  I'll keep selling spells until I have a nice bank account, then after prices drop I'll go buy what I need and level up.  For once in my life, it will go the other way.  I will not pay the huge prices then see them hit the floor after I have it.  I saw CoTH for 50pp the other day in the Bazaar...<br>
<br>
To be quite frank, I didn't buy the original game and 4 expansions so I could be doomed to remain in 1.  Only mobs level 55+ con dark blue to a 65.  I would gain 5 players levels, and lose 10 levels of NPC exp.  That... SUCKS.<br>
<br>
None of my old focus gear works on the new spells (Obulus Death Shroud, Enshrouded Veil, Steel Wristband of Strategy, Rokyls Channeling Crystal, Drachnid Thyxl etc.).  So my gear becomes partially obsolete.  That sucks too.<br>
<br>
New pets are better then epic, BUT only situationally.  In some cases epic is better and epic remains the best all around pet.  I left the ubor raid guild I was in because I was tired of greed.  Now I don't do raids very often so I don't need a level 60 pet that can land spells on that level 65 mob.  Even when I do fight a mob like that, I'm not useless, just not as usefull.<br>
<br>
Want to know what I have seen for the past month now?  How much fun have I been having? TONS!!! BEST TIME EVER IN MY MAGES CAREER!!  If I want a solo spot, Everything is open.  Fungus grove, Ankheva, Maidens Eye, Efreeti camp in Sol B, Lord or King in L. Guk, Bank in Kael, etc.  I even zoned into Velks to find nearly all camps open and dark blue mobs there just for me!  <br>
<br>
I get fantastic EXP and LOOT at the Efreeti camp.  I can clear the whole camp (~14 dark blue mobs) inside of the 22 min respawn time.  It must be around a full yellow in an hour or less.  Seems really fast.  Plus I keep selling Eboots for 3k or Djarns rings for 5k and all the crap loot for ~400 when I'm logging for the night.<br>
<br>
Hey other mages on Solusek Ro, thanks for dinging to 65 and clearing out of all my favorite spots!<br>
<br>
It's not like I lost my grouping ability either.  Mages are in high demand now, and the gear I have makes me very efficient with my current spell set.  The other day, 6 of us grouped up in Plane of Growth to kill Treah, the named Treant.  She must have had 100k, or something close.  Tons of HP and hit for 700's.  We had a cleric, a shaman, a chanter and 3 mages.  One of the mages was level 65 with epic.  He used his air pet and we chatted quite alot as we fought.  He got to level 65 fast enough, sure.  But he only now has like 5 PoP spells in total.  He lost tons of zones to fight in, and has nearly no benefit.  With my focus items, AA points (instead of exp in levels) I was outdamaging him and my epic pet with buffs and items was pushing 6k hp and tanking for all 3 pets.  It held aggro due to level, and mitigated damage nearly as well as the others.  Due to that and the 50 point DS the group was very happy to have epic as the main tank.  We Easily killed Treah.<br>
<br>
I know many of you will say &quot;that mage is an idiot, levels own&quot;  Well to some of you that's true.  From my current drop rate I would say it will be awhile until I get all the PoP spells.  I don't see much reason to ding higher with no spells.  I don't want to lose all the zones I can go in now.  I don't want to make my hard earned focus items useless.  I don't want to spend mind numbing hours at camps for parchments, or pay 8k per in the bazaar.<br>
<br>
Thanks for PoP verant, best thing that ever happened to me. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
