<br>
I can follow your reasons, for some time I thought I would just stay 60 also. I got some AA points in a few weeks, and earned cash. Yes, the situation with many exp camps in the old world is just as you describe it.<br>
<br>
Then however I found that I didnt want to solo anymore (this was the prime reason for me to stay 60 before). I have solo'ed most of my career to 60. Now I wanted some change, and PoP offers this.<br>
<br>
Yes, you cant solo anymore there, but you dont need to. In one regard the developers were right about PoP, advancement &quot;feels&quot; right there. I am currently going for 62 with 90% normal exp, and got about one yellow bub in three or so hours (in PoD). After the endless exp grind to 60, this just feels good with a FULL group. I will go on slowly, getting some exp and some AA points at the same time.<br>
<br>
I found it very worth to change my style and group again. You may be sceptic about losing hunting grounds for exp, but if you (as you describe) want cash...higher levels dont you in the old world zones. If you want exp again...go to the planes and get it.<br>
<br>
I dont look back.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
