<br>
On the other hand, leveling from 62-65 is not as attractive an option.  Only one spell (black steel) is very enticing at all in the 63-64 ranks (for those of us who don't use the pet heal solo strategy), and at 65, only sun vortex and the earth pet are attractive.  Still, assuming one could get all these spells (which, for those of us not in raiding guilds, is not at all a safe assumption), the jump from 62-65 does not benefit one nearly as much as the jump from 60-62.  The 62 water pet does more damage than any of the other pets; I crit for 4k+ with FoT, more than I would with sun vortex or black steel; no focus items are unattainable at 62; etc.  The only real drawback is that I can't train HoE until 63, but HoE is so situational, I don't miss it.<br>
